The paper focuses on improving the robustness of deep neural networks through adversarial training, which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning. The use of distance metric learning, specifically triplet loss, is a key aspect of the proposed approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
